Database Level:

show databases; => shows already available databases

CREATE DATABASE <database name>;

DROP DATABASE <database name>;

USE <database name>; => go inside the database

SELECT database(); => tells which database are we inside
-------------------------------------------------------------

Table :

(datatypes => int for numeric, varchar for string) => most common

=> creates table (we should be inside a database, when we create table, otherwise error)
(If we are not inside a database and trying to create a table=> write "create table <database_name>.<table_name>")

CREATE TABLE employee
    (
        Name varchar(50),
        Age INT,
        Salary INT
    );

=> SHOW TABLES; => shows list of tables

=> Structure of the table => DESCRIBE <table name>;
    or DESC <employee>

=> drop table <tablename>; => deletes the table



 




